You are developing the JYC project itself (bootstrapping).

## Critical Safety: Build/Deploy Operations
AI must use TWO-PHASE CONFIRMATION for ALL build/deploy operations:

Phase 1 - Present Plan:
- List ALL commands that will be executed
- Explain what each command does
- State potential risks (e.g., "build will take 2-3 min", "deploy will restart your session")

Phase 2 - Wait for Approval:
- Ask user to type "yes" or "proceed" to continue
- If user responds with anything else, ABORT the operation
- Only execute commands after receiving explicit "yes" or "proceed"

CRITICAL: Never execute build/deploy commands without explicit user approval.

## Repository
The JYC git repository should be at: ./jyc/
If not yet cloned: git clone https://github.com/kingye/jyc.git
You can use HTTP/HTTPS proxy if required: proxy.sha.sap.corp:8080
Environment variable GH_TOKEN should be set if you need to push branches or create PRs on GitHub.

## Git Rules
- NEVER run `git config user.name` or `git config user.email` (local or global). The git identity is pre-configured by the container. Setting it locally will cause wrong author on commits.
- NEVER run `git config --global` for any setting. Global config is managed by the container startup script.

## Development Workflow
- Always create a feature branch: git checkout -b feat/<name>
- After changes, run tests: cd jyc && cargo test
- Commit with clear messages describing what changed and why
- Push immediately after committing (do not leave unpushed commits)
- Push and create PR when instructed

## Build Environment
- The source is bind-mounted from the host (macOS) into the container (Linux)
- CARGO_TARGET_DIR is set to /tmp/jyc-target to avoid cross-platform conflicts with the host's target/ directory
- Do NOT build into ./target/ directly — always use the CARGO_TARGET_DIR environment variable (already set)
- Rust is pre-installed in the dev image. If using production image, install on-demand:
  `curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y && source "$HOME/.cargo/env"`

## Build (when instructed)
Follow TWO-PHASE CONFIRMATION above before executing.
1. Ensure Rust is installed (see above)
2. cd jyc && cargo test
3. cargo build --release
4. $CARGO_TARGET_DIR/release/jyc --version
5. Report: version, binary size, test results

## Deploy (when instructed)
Follow TWO-PHASE CONFIRMATION above before executing.
WARNING: Deploy causes JYC to restart. Your session will be interrupted.
1. Verify $CARGO_TARGET_DIR/release/jyc exists
2. Send the reply FIRST using the reply_message tool — confirm deployment is starting and report build results
3. AFTER the reply is sent, run the deploy commands:
   ```
   cp $CARGO_TARGET_DIR/release/jyc /usr/local/bin/jyc && s6-svc -r /run/service/jyc
   ```
4. STOP immediately after running the deploy command. Do NOT run any more commands.
   A startup notification email confirms the new version is running.

WARNING: Do NOT send the reply AFTER the deploy command — the process will be dead and the reply will fail.
WARNING: Do NOT run the deploy command multiple times — one restart is sufficient.

## Build and Deploy (when instructed)
Follow TWO-PHASE CONFIRMATION above before executing.
1. Run Build steps (test + compile)
2. Run Deploy steps (reply first, then cp + restart, then STOP)

